DRG ARRIVAL FOR A X-WIND LANDING, THE PILOT MADE A HIGH APPROACH AND USED FULL 
FLAPS TO STEEPEN HIS DSCNT OVER TREES NEAR THE APPROACH END OF THE RUNWAY. HE 
STATED THAT THE TOUCHDOWN WAS NORMAL, BUT BEFORE HE COULD RAISE THE 
FLAPS, THE X-WIND PUSHED THE PLANE TO THE LEFT. SUBSEQUENTLY, THE AIRCRAFT 
ENCOUNTERED A SNOWBANK AND NOSED OVER. 
